race.description: Tab Quaddie Boost Country Boosted Hcp
race.comment: MARINE GIRL (10) led and just missed here first-up on a dry track and then won a 58 at Orange by 4L on a heavy track. She's been substantially improved by the Olive yard and will be fitter again. Has plenty of scope for improvement and is well placed to go back-to-back. FALCON GOLD (5) found more like his best leading and winning a Sapphire Coast Maiden by 2.6L. Draws out but has gate speed and no surprise to see him in the finish. MAN FROM BRUSSELLS (6) creates interest first up. He's a course specialist who maps well and 3x winning rider Matt Cahill continues his association with the gelding. Should be ready to go and has to be considered. VAINSTREAM (3) is a veteran deep into his campaign. Didn't finish it off in a 65 at Canberra last time, but his form leading into that was good enough to suggest he can run well.
